A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Joint Study Committee on Funding for Next Generation 9-1-1 Sustainability;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia's current 9-1-1 funding model was created and authorized
4 by the Georgia General Assembly in 1977, at a time when almost every home and business
5 had landline telephone service; and
6 WHEREAS, the current telecommunications landscape has changed substantially since 1977
7 and now the number of mobile phones and Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) accounts
8 outnumber the landline telephones in service in this state; and
9 WHEREAS, in 1977, the General Assembly established a maximum fee of $1.50 per landline
10 telephone to be used for funding 9-1-1 centers; and
11 WHEREAS, the number of telephones in use statewide, regardless of the technology utilized,
12 has increased significantly since 1977; and
13 WHEREAS, technologies are on the horizon that will allow 9-1-1 centers to be contacted by
14 data sessions and text messages originating from mobile telephones and other devices; and
