15 WHEREAS, Part 4 of Article 2 of Chapter 5 of Title 46 of the Official Code of Georgia
16 Annotated, the "Georgia Emergency Telephone Number 9-1-1 Service Act of 1977," which
17 provides for 9-1-1 funding, has been amended several times since 1977 in an attempt to keep
18 up with changes in technology; and
19 WHEREAS, most of the calls to 9-1-1 centers today originate from mobile telephones and
20 other devices; and
21 WHEREAS, the funding mechanism for 9-1-1 centers may need to be updated to reflect
22 today's environment; and
23 WHEREAS, a comprehensive review of this state's 9-1-1 funding provisions is needed in
24 order to study and identify any reforms necessary to provide adequate funding for
25 maintaining effective and efficient 9-1-1 centers in order to ensure the public safety of all
26 citizens of Georgia.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF
28 GEORGIA:
29 (1) Creation of joint study committee. There is created the Joint Study Committee on
30 Funding for Next Generation 9-1-1 Sustainability.
31 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of the following
32 members:
33 (A) The President of the Senate shall appoint five members of the Senate as members
34 of the committee, one of whom shall be a member of the Senate Regulated Industries
35 and Utilities Committee and one of whom shall be a member of the Senate Public
36 Safety Committee. The President of the Senate shall also designate one of such
37 members as cochairperson;
