38 (B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint five members of the
39 House of Representatives as members of the committee, one of whom shall be a
40 member of the House Committee on Energy, Utilities, and Telecommunications and
41 one of whom shall be a member of the House Committee on Public Safety and
42 Homeland Security. The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall also designate
43 one of such members as cochairperson;
44 (C) The executive director of the Georgia Emergency Communications Authority, or
45 his or her designee;
46 (D) The director of the Georgia Emergency Management and Homeland Security
47 Agency, or his or her designee;
48 (E) The commissioner of the Department of Revenue, or his or her designee;
49 (F) The president of the Georgia Municipal Association, or his or her designee; and
50 (E) The president of the Association County Commissioners of Georgia, or his or her
51 designee.
52 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
53 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
54 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
55 (4) Meetings. The cochairpersons shall call all meetings of the committee. The
56 committee may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem
57 necessary or convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform
58 its duties, and accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
59 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
60 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
61 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
62 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
63 or state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the committee,
64 but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the performance of their
