65 duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they are reimbursed for
66 expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
67 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
68 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
69 specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia
70 Annotated, as well as the mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state
71 employees.
72 (D) The allowances and expenses authorized by this resolution shall not be received
73 by any member of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are
74 authorized. Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come
75 from funds appropriated to the House of Representatives and Senate; except that funds
76 for the reimbursement of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members,
77 and state employees shall come from funds appropriated to or otherwise available to
78 their respective agencies.
79 (6) Report.
80 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
81 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the cochairpersons shall file a report of the
82 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
83 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
84 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
85 proposed legislation, the cochairpersons shall file the report, subject to
86 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
87 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
88 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
89 A report so approved shall be signed by the cochairpersons of the committee and filed
90 with the Secretary of the Senate and the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
